summary:
• Cessation of Securities: 96,582 HGHAA Performance Rights lapsed due to unmet conditions (employment cessation of participant).
  • Date of Cessation: 03/04/2025.
  • No Consideration Paid: Entity did not compensate for the lapse.
  • Post-Cessation Issued Capital:
  • Quoted: 940,099,841 HGH ordinary shares.
  • Unquoted: 1,149,148 HGHAA Performance Rights, 459,070 HGHAB Treasury Stock, 100,000 HGHAC Medium Term Notes.

No material trading or capital markets impact identified (minor dilution reduction from lapse).

• 2Q25 Sales Performance: 402 total sales (222 new, 180 resales), a record quarter.
  • 1H25 Sales Growth: 692 total sales, up 18% YoY vs. 1H24.
  • Regional Sales: 46.7% of sales from outside Auckland/Wellington/Christchurch.
  • FY25 Guidance: On track to deliver 650–730 homes, including new village developments in Cambridge (NZ) and Cranbourne North (AU).
  • HY25 Results Date: 28 August 2025.

No capital markets actions or material financial data (e.g., cash balance, raising details) identified.
